Blog Post Management System (Backend)

This is a simple backend API for a Blog Post Management System built using Node.js, Express, and MongoDB
It allows users to create, read, update, delete, search, and export blog posts.

---

Tech Stack

- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB + Mongoose
- Zod (for validation)
- json2csv (for CSV export)
- Nodemon

---

What this project does

Basically, this backend handles all blog operations like:

- Creating a blog post
- Viewing all blog posts
- Updating a blog post
- Deleting a blog post
- Searching blogs
- Pagination support
- Exporting blogs to CSV

---

API Endpoints

Blogs

POST /api/blogs → Create a blog
GET /api/blogs → Get all blogs (with search + pagination)
GET /api/blogs/:id → Get single blog
PUT /api/blogs/:id → Update blog
DELETE /api/blogs/:id → Delete blog

---

CSV Export

GET /api/blogs/export/csv

This will download all blogs as a CSV file.

---

Search & Pagination

You can search blogs like this:

GET /api/blogs?search=react

And use pagination like this:

GET /api/blogs?page=1&limit=5

You can also combine both:

GET /api/blogs?search=react&page=1&limit=5

---

Database

- MongoDB is used for storing blog data
- Mongoose is used to define schema and interact with DB

---

Setup Instructions

Install dependencies

```bash
npm install

2. Create .env file
MONGODB_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
PORT=8000

3. Start the server
npm run dev

What I learned while building this
How REST APIs work
Pagination using skip & limit
Searching with MongoDB queries
CSV export functionality
Clean backend structure with controllers and utils
Input validation using Zod

👨‍💻 Author
